Package com.example.vybe.AddEdit

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LocationSelectionDialog.OnLocationSelectedListener  
    VibeCarouselDialogFragment.OnVibeSelectedListener  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AddEditController
    This class sets initial Vibe Event information in the AddEditVibeEventActivity and uploads and saves the new Vibe Event information to Firestore This class also implements the singleton pattern to ensure there is only ever one instance of the class throughout application use
    AddEditVibeEventActivity
    This Activity displays the screen for a user to add a vibe event, or edit an existing vibe event by adding or modifying the different vibe attributes
    ImageFieldFragment
    This class represents a fragment that allows a user to select and view an image from their device storage/gallery
    LocationSelectionDialog
    This dialog allows the user to select a location to be added to the vibe
    SocSitFieldFragment
    This fragment represents a custom spinner to allow a user to select a social situation to add to a Vibe Event
    VibeCarouselDialogFragment
    VibeCarouselDialogFragment extends a DialogFragment and serves as a custom picker for a user to decide which Vibe they want to have added to a Vibe Event Functionality is similar to that of a DatePickerDialog
